The following are major news items in leading Kenyan
newspapers today. Kenya Times -- Kenyan Vice President and Minister for
Planning and National Development George Saitoti has defended the
country from wholesale condemnation as a corrupt state. Daily Nation --
Zimbabwean President Robert Mugabe's government has given farmers a
list of 1,772 mostly white-owned farms which it plans to turn over to
landless black peasants. -- Rival clans are fighting in southern
Somalia while relief agencies struggle to get aid to more than 200,000
people marooned by the country's worst floods in living memory and
rescue those in danger. East African Standard -- The Kenyan government
declared Wednesday the North Eastern province a flood disaster zone,
following persistent heavy rains which have caused loss of lives and
destruction of property and disruption of communication in the affected
areas.
